Once again discovering unexpected #DDR remnants on a Sunday bike ride🚲: Memorial to revolutionary fighters for anti-fascism and socialism; grave of Chris Gueffroy, final victim of the Berlin Wall; and entrance to the DDR’s former largest children’s home - Baumschulenweg, #Berlin https://t.co/QRp4WTDXuh

#OTD in 1913: Johannisthal air disaster (Germany). German Navy Airship LZ18 explodes in Johannisthal airfield (Berlin) all 28 crew die. During a test, Hydrogen being vented was sucked into the forward engine and ignited, causing the airship to explode and burn. https://t.co/gXX65BJjq5
@DHeuwer Sushi and Friends Berlin/Johannisthal

Julius Klinger was a talented illustrator and graphic designer from Austria (1876-1942), sadly a victim of the Holocaust. I love his poster for Around Berlin, a 1912 air show at Berlin’s first airfield in Johannisthal, a borough of Treptow-Köpenick. https://t.co/YZp9zfAXaF

Over 25% of all 48,000 German #WW1 aeroplanes were produced in #Berlin: at Flugplatz #Johannisthal - Germany's 1st airfield & 2nd GER airfield for powered aircraft after Darmstad.

After the lost war and decision to clip Germany's wings, the airfield became an aicraft cemetery. https://t.co/5qGBJrraaA
